#. <section class="sutta" id="mn141"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn141:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 141"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 141"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn141:0.2"
msgid "Saccavibhaṅgasutta"
msgstr "The Analysis of the Truths"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.248"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "mn141:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "mn141:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati isipatane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Benares, in the deer park at "
"Isipatana."

msgctxt "mn141:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn141:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn141:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn141:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Tathāgatena, bhikkhave, arahatā sammāsambuddhena bārāṇasiyaṃ isipatane "
"migadāye anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā "
"brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“Near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana, the Realized One, the "
"perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha rolled forth the supreme Wheel of "
"Dhamma. And that wheel cannot be rolled back by any ascetic or brahmin or "
"god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world."

msgctxt "mn141:2.2"
msgid ""
"catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ ācikkhanā desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā "
"vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It is the teaching, advocating, establishing, clarifying, analyzing, and "
"revealing of the four noble truths."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:4.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:3.1"
msgid ""
"Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa ācikkhanā desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā "
"vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ, dukkhasamudayassa ariyasaccassa ācikkhanā desanā "
"paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ, dukkhanirodhassa "
"ariyasaccassa ācikkhanā desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā vibhajanā "
"uttānīkammaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasaccassa ācikkhanā "
"desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The noble truths of suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of "
"suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "mn141:3.2"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatena, bhikkhave, arahatā sammāsambuddhena bārāṇasiyaṃ isipatane "
"migadāye anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā "
"brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana, the Realized One, the perfected "
"one, the fully awakened Buddha rolled forth the supreme Wheel of Dhamma. And "
"that wheel cannot be rolled back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or "
"Brahmā or by anyone in the world."

msgctxt "mn141:3.3"
msgid ""
"imesaṃ catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ ācikkhanā desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā "
"vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It is the teaching, advocating, establishing, clarifying, analyzing, and "
"revealing of the four noble truths."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:5.1"
msgid "Sevatha, bhikkhave, sāriputtamoggallāne;"
msgstr ""
"Mendicants, you should cultivate friendship with Sāriputta and Moggallāna."

msgctxt "mn141:5.2"
msgid "bhajatha, bhikkhave, sāriputtamoggallāne."
msgstr "You should associate with Sāriputta and Moggallāna."

msgctxt "mn141:5.3"
msgid "Paṇḍitā bhikkhū anuggāhakā sabrahmacārīnaṃ."
msgstr "They’re astute, and they support their spiritual companions."

#. VAR: janetā → janetti (bj) | janettī (pts1)
msgctxt "mn141:5.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, janetā, evaṃ sāriputto;"
msgstr "Sāriputta is just like the mother who gives birth,"

msgctxt "mn141:5.5"
msgid "seyyathāpi jātassa āpādetā, evaṃ moggallāno."
msgstr "while Moggallāna is like the one who raises the child."

msgctxt "mn141:5.6"
msgid "Sāriputto, bhikkhave, sotāpattiphale vineti, moggallāno uttamatthe."
msgstr ""
"Sāriputta guides people to the fruit of stream-entry, Moggallāna to the "
"highest goal."

msgctxt "mn141:5.7"
msgid ""
"Sāriputto, bhikkhave, pahoti cattāri ariyasaccāni vitthārena ācikkhituṃ "
"desetuṃ paññāpetuṃ paṭṭhapetuṃ vivarituṃ vibhajituṃ uttānīkātun”ti."
msgstr ""
"Sāriputta is able to teach, assert, establish, clarify, analyze, and reveal "
"the four noble truths.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:6.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn141:6.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his "
"dwelling."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.249"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:7.1"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto acirapakkantassa bhagavato bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then soon after the Buddha left, Venerable Sāriputta said to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn141:7.2"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn141:7.3"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn141:7.4"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Tathāgatena, āvuso, arahatā sammāsambuddhena bārāṇasiyaṃ isipatane migadāye "
"anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā "
"devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“Near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana, the Realized One, the "
"perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha rolled forth the supreme Wheel of "
"Dhamma. And that wheel cannot be rolled back by any ascetic or brahmin or "
"god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world."

msgctxt "mn141:8.2"
msgid ""
"catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ ācikkhanā desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā "
"vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It is the teaching, advocating, establishing, clarifying, analyzing, and "
"revealing of the four noble truths."

msgctxt "mn141:8.3"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:9.1"
msgid ""
"Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa ācikkhanā desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā "
"vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ, dukkhasamudayassa ariyasaccassa ācikkhanā desanā "
"paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ, dukkhanirodhassa "
"ariyasaccassa ācikkhanā desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā vibhajanā "
"uttānīkammaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasaccassa ācikkhanā "
"desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The noble truths of suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of "
"suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:10.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the noble truth of suffering?"

msgctxt "mn141:10.2"
msgid ""
"Jātipi dukkhā, jarāpi dukkhā, maraṇampi dukkhaṃ, "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsāpi dukkhā, yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi "
"dukkhaṃ; saṅkhittena pañcupādānakkhandhā dukkhā."
msgstr ""
"Rebirth is suffering; old age is suffering; death is suffering; sorrow, "
"lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are suffering; association with the "
"disliked is suffering; separation from the liked is suffering; not getting "
"what you wish for is suffering. In brief, the five grasping aggregates are "
"suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:11.1"
msgid "Katamā cāvuso, jāti?"
msgstr "And what is rebirth?"

msgctxt "mn141:11.2"
msgid ""
"Yā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhi tamhi sattanikāye jāti sañjāti okkanti "
"abhinibbatti khandhānaṃ pātubhāvo āyatanānaṃ paṭilābho, "
msgstr ""
"The rebirth, inception, conception, reincarnation, manifestation of the "
"aggregates, and acquisition of the sense fields of the various sentient "
"beings in the various orders of sentient beings. "

msgctxt "mn141:11.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘jāti’."
msgstr "This is called rebirth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:12.1"
msgid "Katamā cāvuso, jarā?"
msgstr "And what is old age?"

msgctxt "mn141:12.2"
msgid ""
"Yā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhi tamhi sattanikāye jarā jīraṇatā khaṇḍiccaṃ "
"pāliccaṃ valittacatā āyuno saṃhāni indriyānaṃ paripāko, "
msgstr ""
"The old age, decrepitude, broken teeth, grey hair, wrinkly skin, diminished "
"vitality, and failing faculties of the various sentient beings in the "
"various orders of sentient beings. "

msgctxt "mn141:12.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘jarā’."
msgstr "This is called old age."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:13.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, maraṇaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is death?"

msgctxt "mn141:13.2"
msgid ""
"Yā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhā tamhā sattanikāyā cuti cavanatā bhedo "
"antaradhānaṃ maccu maraṇaṃ kālaṅkiriyā khandhānaṃ bhedo kaḷevarassa nikkhepo "
"jīvitindriyassupacchedo, "
msgstr ""
"The passing away, perishing, disintegration, demise, mortality, death, "
"decease, breaking up of the aggregates, laying to rest of the corpse, and "
"cutting off of the life faculty of the various sentient beings in the "
"various orders of sentient beings. "

msgctxt "mn141:13.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘maraṇaṃ’."
msgstr "This is called death."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:14.1"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, soko?"
msgstr "And what is sorrow?"

msgctxt "mn141:14.2"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, āvuso, aññataraññatarena byasanena samannāgatassa aññataraññatarena "
"dukkhadhammena phuṭṭhassa soko socanā socitattaṃ antosoko antoparisoko, "
msgstr ""
"The sorrow, sorrowing, state of sorrow, inner sorrow, inner deep sorrow in "
"someone who has undergone misfortune, who has experienced suffering. "

msgctxt "mn141:14.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘soko’."
msgstr "This is called sorrow."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.250"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:15.1"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, paridevo?"
msgstr "And what is lamentation?"

msgctxt "mn141:15.2"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, āvuso, aññataraññatarena byasanena samannāgatassa aññataraññatarena "
"dukkhadhammena phuṭṭhassa ādevo paridevo ādevanā paridevanā ādevitattaṃ "
"paridevitattaṃ, "
msgstr ""
"The wail, lament, wailing, lamenting, state of wailing and lamentation in "
"someone who has undergone misfortune, who has experienced suffering. "

msgctxt "mn141:15.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘paridevo’."
msgstr "This is called lamentation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:16.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, dukkhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is pain?"

msgctxt "mn141:16.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, āvuso, kāyikaṃ dukkhaṃ kāyikaṃ asātaṃ kāyasamphassajaṃ dukkhaṃ "
"asātaṃ vedayitaṃ, "
msgstr ""
"Physical pain, physical displeasure, the painful, unpleasant feeling that’s "
"born from physical contact. "

msgctxt "mn141:16.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘dukkhaṃ’."
msgstr "This is called pain."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:17.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, domanassaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is sadness?"

msgctxt "mn141:17.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, āvuso, cetasikaṃ dukkhaṃ cetasikaṃ asātaṃ manosamphassajaṃ dukkhaṃ "
"asātaṃ vedayitaṃ, "
msgstr ""
"Mental pain, mental displeasure, the painful, unpleasant feeling that’s born "
"from mind contact. "

msgctxt "mn141:17.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘domanassaṃ’."
msgstr "This is called sadness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:18.1"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, upāyāso?"
msgstr "And what is distress?"

msgctxt "mn141:18.2"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, āvuso, aññataraññatarena byasanena samannāgatassa aññataraññatarena "
"dukkhadhammena phuṭṭhassa āyāso upāyāso āyāsitattaṃ upāyāsitattaṃ, "
msgstr ""
"The stress, distress, state of stress and distress in someone who has "
"undergone misfortune, who has experienced suffering. "

msgctxt "mn141:18.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘upāyāso’."
msgstr "This is called distress."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:19.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is ‘not getting what you wish for is suffering’?"

msgctxt "mn141:19.2"
msgid "Jātidhammānaṃ, āvuso, sattānaṃ evaṃ icchā uppajjati:"
msgstr "In sentient beings who are liable to be reborn, such a wish arises:"

msgctxt "mn141:19.3"
msgid "‘aho vata mayaṃ na jātidhammā assāma; na ca vata no jāti āgaccheyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, if only we were not liable to be reborn! If only rebirth would not come "
"to us!’"

msgctxt "mn141:19.4"
msgid "Na kho panetaṃ icchāya pattabbaṃ. "
msgstr "But you can’t get that by wishing. "

msgctxt "mn141:19.5"
msgid "Idampi: ‘yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ’."
msgstr "This is: ‘not getting what you wish for is suffering.’"

msgctxt "mn141:19.6"
msgid "Jarādhammānaṃ, āvuso, sattānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "In sentient beings who are liable to grow old …"

msgctxt "mn141:19.7"
msgid "byādhidhammānaṃ, āvuso, sattānaṃ …"
msgstr "fall ill …"

msgctxt "mn141:19.8"
msgid "maraṇadhammānaṃ, āvuso, sattānaṃ …"
msgstr "die …"

msgctxt "mn141:19.9"
msgid ""
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammānaṃ, āvuso, sattānaṃ evaṃ icchā "
"uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"experience sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, such a wish "
"arises:"

msgctxt "mn141:19.10"
msgid ""
"‘aho vata mayaṃ na sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā assāma; na ca "
"vata no sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā āgaccheyyun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, if only we were not liable to experience sorrow, lamentation, pain, "
"sadness, and distress! If only sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and "
"distress would not come to us!’"

msgctxt "mn141:19.11"
msgid "Na kho panetaṃ icchāya pattabbaṃ. "
msgstr "But you can’t get that by wishing. "

msgctxt "mn141:19.12"
msgid "Idampi: ‘yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ’."
msgstr "This is: ‘not getting what you wish for is suffering.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:20.1"
msgid "Katame cāvuso, saṅkhittena pañcupādānakkhandhā dukkhā?"
msgstr "And what is ‘in brief, the five grasping aggregates are suffering’?"

msgctxt "mn141:20.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho. "
msgstr ""
"They are the grasping aggregates that consist of form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness. "

msgctxt "mn141:20.3"
msgid "Ime vuccantāvuso: ‘saṅkhittena pañcupādānakkhandhā dukkhā’."
msgstr "This is called ‘in brief, the five grasping aggregates are suffering.’"

msgctxt "mn141:20.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ’."
msgstr "This is called the noble truth of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.251"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:21.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, dukkhasamudayaṃ ariyasaccaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the noble truth of the origin of suffering?"

#. VAR: ponobbhavikā → ponobhavikā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn141:21.2"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ taṇhā ponobbhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"It’s the craving that leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and "
"greed, looking for enjoyment in various different realms. That is,"

msgctxt "mn141:21.3"
msgid "kāmataṇhā bhavataṇhā vibhavataṇhā,"
msgstr ""
"craving for sensual pleasures, craving to continue existence, and craving to "
"end existence."

msgctxt "mn141:21.4"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘dukkhasamudayaṃ ariyasaccaṃ’."
msgstr "This is called the noble truth of the origin of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
#. VAR: dukkhanirodhaṃ → dukkhanirodho (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn141:22.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, dukkhanirodhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the noble truth of the cessation of suffering?"

msgctxt "mn141:22.2"
msgid ""
"Yo tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodho cāgo paṭinissaggo mutti anālayo,"
msgstr ""
"It’s the fading away and cessation of that very same craving with nothing "
"left over; giving it away, letting it go, releasing it, and not adhering to "
"it."

msgctxt "mn141:22.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘dukkhanirodhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ’."
msgstr "This is called the noble truth of the cessation of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:23.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"And what is the noble truth of the practice that leads to the cessation of "
"suffering?"

msgctxt "mn141:23.2"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "mn141:23.3"
msgid ""
"sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, "
"sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:24.1"
msgid "Katamā cāvuso, sammādiṭṭhi?"
msgstr "And what is right view?"

msgctxt "mn141:24.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, āvuso, dukkhe ñāṇaṃ, dukkhasamudaye ñāṇaṃ, dukkhanirodhe ñāṇaṃ, "
"dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ñāṇaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"Knowing about suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of "
"suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "mn141:24.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘sammādiṭṭhi’."
msgstr "This is called right view."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:25.1"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, sammāsaṅkappo?"
msgstr "And what is right thought?"

msgctxt "mn141:25.2"
msgid "Nekkhammasaṅkappo, abyāpādasaṅkappo, avihiṃsāsaṅkappo,"
msgstr "Thoughts of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness."

msgctxt "mn141:25.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘sammāsaṅkappo’."
msgstr "This is called right thought."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:26.1"
msgid "Katamā cāvuso, sammāvācā?"
msgstr "And what is right speech?"

msgctxt "mn141:26.2"
msgid ""
"Musāvādā veramaṇī, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī, "
"samphappalāpā veramaṇī,"
msgstr ""
"Refraining from lying, divisive speech, harsh speech, and talking nonsense."

msgctxt "mn141:26.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘sammāvācā’."
msgstr "This is called right speech."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:27.1"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, sammākammanto?"
msgstr "And what is right action?"

msgctxt "mn141:27.2"
msgid "Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī, adinnādānā veramaṇī, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī,"
msgstr ""
"Refraining from killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct."

msgctxt "mn141:27.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘sammākammanto’."
msgstr "This is called right action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:28.1"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, sammāājīvo?"
msgstr "And what is right livelihood?"

msgctxt "mn141:28.2"
msgid "Idhāvuso, ariyasāvako micchāājīvaṃ pahāya sammāājīvena jīvikaṃ kappeti,"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple gives up wrong livelihood and earns a living by "
"right livelihood."

msgctxt "mn141:28.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘sammāājīvo’."
msgstr "This is called right livelihood."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.252"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:29.1"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, sammāvāyāmo?"
msgstr "And what is right effort?"

msgctxt "mn141:29.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya "
"chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati, "
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts "
"the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise. "

msgctxt "mn141:29.3"
msgid ""
"uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati "
"vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati, "
msgstr ""
"They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so "
"that bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen are given up. "

msgctxt "mn141:29.4"
msgid ""
"anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ "
"ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati, "
msgstr ""
"They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so "
"that skillful qualities arise. "

msgctxt "mn141:29.5"
msgid ""
"uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya "
"bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ "
"paggaṇhāti padahati,"
msgstr ""
"They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so "
"that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, "
"mature, and are completed by development."

msgctxt "mn141:29.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘sammāvāyāmo’."
msgstr "This is called right effort."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:30.1"
msgid "Katamā cāvuso, sammāsati?"
msgstr "And what is right mindfulness?"

msgctxt "mn141:30.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "mn141:30.3"
msgid "Vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "mn141:30.4"
msgid "citte cittānupassī viharati …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "mn141:30.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "mn141:30.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘sammāsati’."
msgstr "This is called right mindfulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya31"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:31.1"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, sammāsamādhi?"
msgstr "And what is right immersion?"

msgctxt "mn141:31.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ "
"savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "mn141:31.3"
msgid ""
"vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,"
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of "
"immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without "
"placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "mn141:31.4"
msgid "pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third "
"absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

msgctxt "mn141:31.5"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,"
msgstr ""
"Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they "
"enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with "
"pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "mn141:31.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘sammāsamādhi’."
msgstr "This is called right immersion."

msgctxt "mn141:31.7"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccatāvuso: ‘dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ’."
msgstr ""
"This is called the noble truth of the practice that leads to the cessation "
"of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya32"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:32.1"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatenāvuso, arahatā sammāsambuddhena bārāṇasiyaṃ isipatane migadāye "
"anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā "
"devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana, the Realized One, the perfected "
"one, the fully awakened Buddha rolled forth the supreme Wheel of Dhamma. And "
"that wheel cannot be rolled back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or "
"Brahmā or by anyone in the world."

msgctxt "mn141:32.2"
msgid ""
"imesaṃ catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ ācikkhanā desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā "
"vibhajanā uttānīkamman”ti."
msgstr ""
"It is the teaching, advocating, establishing, clarifying, analyzing, and "
"revealing of the four noble truths.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn141:32.3"
msgid "Idamavoca āyasmā sāriputto."
msgstr "That’s what Venerable Sāriputta said."

msgctxt "mn141:32.4"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what Sāriputta said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn141:32.5"
msgid "Saccavibhaṅgasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
